<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id7a2eb9d3-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5" identifier="/us/usc/t16/s7912"><num value="7912">§ 7912.</num><heading> Federal land open to hunting, fishing, and recreational shooting</heading><subsection style="-uslm-lc:I19" class="indent2 firstIndent-2" id="id7a2eb9d4-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5" identifier="/us/usc/t16/s7912/a"><num value="a" class="bold">(a)</num><heading class="bold"> In general</heading><content><p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">Subject to subsection (b), Federal land shall be open to hunting, fishing, and recreational shooting, in accordance with applicable law, unless the Secretary concerned closes an area in accordance with <ref href="/us/usc/t16/s7913">section 7913 of this title</ref>.</p>
</content>
</subsection>
<subsection style="-uslm-lc:I19" class="indent2 firstIndent-2" id="id7a2eb9d5-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5" identifier="/us/usc/t16/s7912/b"><num value="b" class="bold">(b)</num><heading class="bold"> Effect of part</heading><content><p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">Nothing in this subchapter opens to hunting, fishing, or recreational shooting any land that is not open to those activities as of <date date="2019-03-12">March 12, 2019</date>.</p>
</content>
</subsection>
<sourceCredit id="id7a2eb9d6-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5">(<ref href="/us/pl/116/9/tIV/s4102">Pub. L. 116–9, title IV, § 4102</ref>, <date date="2019-03-12">Mar. 12, 2019</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/133/757">133 Stat. 757</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
</section>
